---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { siteMeta } from '../data/siteMeta';

const title = `Privacy Policy | ${siteMeta.businessName}`;
const description = `How ${siteMeta.businessName} collects, uses, and protects information from visitors and clients, under Bangladesh's Personal Data Protection Act and the EU GDPR.`;
const lastUpdated = "8 July 2026";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} noindex={true}>
  <section style="padding: 80px 0;">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 750px;">
      <h1 style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 3rem); margin-bottom: 16px;">Privacy Policy</h1>

      <div style="border: 1.5px solid var(--accent-color); border-radius: 6px; padding: 16px 20px; margin-bottom: 40px;">
        <p style="color: var(--accent-color); font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 8px;">⚠ Informed draft — not a substitute for a lawyer</p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 0;">
          This draft reflects the structure and obligations of Bangladesh's Personal Data
          Protection Act, 2026 (PDPA) and the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)
          as generally understood. It has not been reviewed by a lawyer and does not account
          for {siteMeta.businessName}'s exact data flows, retention practices, or whether it
          meets the PDPA's "significant data fiduciary" threshold (which carries extra
          obligations, e.g. appointing a Chief Data Officer). Have a Bangladeshi lawyer
          review this before removing <code>noindex</code> and publishing.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-secondary);">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-top: 30px;">1. Who this policy covers</h2>
      <p>
        This policy applies to visitors of this website, buyers and suppliers we work with,
        and companies we verify. {siteMeta.businessName} is the "data controller" (GDPR) /
        "data fiduciary" (PDPA) for the personal data described below.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-top: 30px;">2. What information we collect</h2>
      <ul style="margin-bottom: 24px;">
        <li>Contact details you give us directly (name, email, phone, company) via the contact form or email</li>
        <li>Correspondence related to a service engagement</li>
        <li>Information gathered during factory/company verification (business registration numbers, addresses, authorized contact details — see our <a href="/companies">Verified Companies</a> pages)</li>
        <li>[Placeholder — add: analytics/cookies if any are in use, e.g. Cloudflare Web Analytics]</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not knowingly collect sensitive personal data (health, biometric, financial
        account details, etc.) through this website. If a service ever requires that,
        [placeholder — describe safeguard, e.g. separate consent, encrypted channel].
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-top: 30px;">3. Why we process it (lawful basis)</h2>
      <p>
        Under GDPR Article 6 and the PDPA's consent-based framework, we rely on:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Consent</strong> — when you submit the contact form or email us directly</li>
        <li><strong>Contract</strong> — to perform a service you've engaged us for</li>
        <li><strong>Legitimate interest</strong> — to maintain accurate verification records that protect other buyers/suppliers from fraud</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-top: 30px;">4. How we store and protect it</h2>
      <p>
        [Placeholder — describe actual storage: where data is hosted, encryption in transit/at
        rest, who has access.] Under the PDPA's data localization rules, certain categories
        (restricted data, or data tied to critical information infrastructure) may require
        at least one synchronized copy stored within Bangladesh — confirm with a lawyer
        whether this applies to {siteMeta.businessName}'s data.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-top: 30px;">5. Retention</h2>
      <p>
        [Placeholder — set an actual retention period.] As a starting reference, the PDPA
        expects processing records to be retained for a minimum of five years; this is a
        floor, not necessarily the right retention period for every category of data you hold.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-top: 30px;">6. Who we share it with</h2>
      <p>
        [Placeholder — e.g. do factories/buyers/suppliers see each other's contact details
        during a transaction? Do any government bodies (BIDA, RJSC, BGMEA, etc.) receive
        data as part of verification, or do we only consult their public records?] We do
        not sell personal data.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-top: 30px;">7. International transfers</h2>
      <p>
        If personal data moves between Bangladesh, the EU, or elsewhere (e.g. a European
        buyer's contact details processed on servers outside the EU), GDPR requires an
        appropriate transfer mechanism (such as Standard Contractual Clauses) unless the
        destination has an adequacy decision. [Placeholder — confirm hosting/processor
        locations with a lawyer to determine what's actually needed here.]
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-top: 30px;">8. Your rights</h2>
      <p>Depending on where you're located, you may have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Access the personal data we hold about you</li>
        <li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
        <li>Request erasure ("right to be forgotten," subject to legal/record-keeping exceptions)</li>
        <li>Receive your data in a portable format (GDPR)</li>
        <li>Object to or opt out of certain processing (both GDPR and PDPA)</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent at any time, without affecting processing done before withdrawal</li>
      </ul>
      <p>To exercise any of these, contact us using the details below.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-top: 30px;">9. Children's data</h2>
      <p>
        This site and our services are intended for business use by adults. We do not
        knowingly collect data from children.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-top: 30px;">10. Breach notification</h2>
      <p>
        [Placeholder — commit to a real process.] GDPR requires notifying the relevant
        authority within 72 hours of becoming aware of a qualifying breach, and affected
        individuals where there's high risk to them; the PDPA imposes its own notification
        duties to Bangladesh's National Data Management Authority.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-top: 30px;">11. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>We'll update the "last updated" date above when this policy changes materially.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-top: 30px;">12. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy, or to exercise a data right:
        <a href={`mailto:${siteMeta.contact.email}`}>{siteMeta.contact.email}</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
